&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;Primary Care 24 is a social enterprise which delivers a range of services on behalf of the NHS.  Our services include urgent and primary care services across Liverpool, Halton, Knowsley St Helens and Sefton.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have 7 practice across South Sefton: Crosby Village, Crossways, Litherland, Seaforth, Netherton, Thornton, Maghull.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join our nursing team working across our practices. You will work as part of our multi-disciplinary team to ensure that our services are safe, caring and effective and meet the requirements of our commissioners,  the Care Quality Commission and other regulatory bodies. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We want to hear from people who are flexible and feel they can meet the challenge of working within a busy, dynamic environment that can prove challenging at times.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The range of services provided by PC24 will provide the successful candidate with an opportunity for further development across Primary Care and Integrated Urgent Care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are interested in this post please contact Stacey Shields, Deputy Director of Urgent Care on Stacey.shields@pc24.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
